    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-03T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-03T03:00:00-05:00" n="423"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d423">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.6362/7–345: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 423<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent—niact</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-03T10:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 3, 1945—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6674. The following reply to the President’s message (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 5117, June 24<note n="1" xml:id="d423fn1">
                        <ref target="#d420">Document No. 420</ref>.</note>) has just been received
                    from the Prime Minister: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_THS1"
                                >Truman</persName>. Personal and top secret.</p>
                        <p>I am in full agreement in principle with your proposal and a similar
                            directive to <persName corresp="#p_MFMSB1">Field Marshal
                                Montgomery</persName> is being prepared. There are certain points on
                            which the Foreign Office are addressing the State <gloss
                                target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>,<note n="2" xml:id="d423fn2">See <ref
                                    target="#d425">document No. 425</ref>.</note> and we should like
                            to have these considered before despatching our telegram.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
